 as a means to prevent disease and effectively manage health disorders, it is the hope of the nearly three dozen contributors to this work that it will enhance the health and well-being of low-income populations throughout the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDiet in disease. 0aNutritionxEvaluation. 0aNutritionzDeveloping countries. 0aNutritionally induced diseaseszDeveloping countriesxPrevention. 7aMEDICAL / Nutrition.2bisacsh  amaternal health, poverty, nutritional status, AIDS, prevantable disease, immunizations.1 aSteyn, Nelia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTemple, Norman J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630440uhttps://doi.org/10.15215/aupress/9781927356111.0140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356128/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles